                            <comment id="13004900" author="xuefuz" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 00:43:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually the problem is not caused by either bincond operator or parser, but by pig&apos;s grammar limitation. Data fields in a literal bag can only have literals. By Pig&apos;s grammar, -1 is not a literal, but an expression.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, parser is happy with C = foreach B generate group, flatten(((COUNT(A) &amp;lt; 1L) ? &lt;/p&gt;
{(1)}
&lt;p&gt; : A.x));.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To solve the problem, Pig grammar needs to be extended.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
